想到每次我们回家写一张新专辑，或者我们有一张专辑在罐头里但还没有向世界展示时，这种感觉真的很可怕。”</p><p>她继续说道：“以一种新的方式展示自己，本质上是在世界面前成长，这可能会让人伤脑筋。每当一支乐队以新的形象、新的心态重新出现时，我认为这是勇敢和酷的，我真的很享受他们的演变。”</p><p>在其他消息中， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hayley-williams-reveals-paramore-are-back-in-the-studio-3489968">威廉姆斯上个月证实三人组已经回到录音室</a>。 “扎克、泰勒和我只是想重新开始创作，”她当时说道。</p><p> “我们渴望这一点已经有一段时间了。不仅是创作过程，还有创作过程中可能出现的隔离层。”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/paramore-announce-artists-for-this-is-why-remix-album-featuring-foals-wet-leg-julien-baker-and-more-3509373">Paramore 宣布《This Is Why》混音专辑的艺术家名单，其中包括 Foals、Wet Leg、Julien Baker 等，该专辑</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
保罗·麦卡特尼推出“A Life In Lyrics”播客，解释披头士乐队的“埃莉诺·里格比” https://www.nme.com/news/music/paul-mccartney-launches-a-life-in-lyrics-podcast-by-explaining-the-beatles-eleanor-rigby-3509327?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=保罗·麦卡特尼通过解释披头士乐队埃莉诺·里格比推出了歌词生活播客Anagricel DuranWed, 04 Oct 2023 17:32:11 +0000 Music NewsNewsRockhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3509327 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="音乐家保罗·麦卡特尼 (Paul McCartney) 于 2016 年 10 月 15 日在加利福尼亚州印第奥的帝国马球场进行沙漠之旅表演。图片来源：凯文·温特/盖蒂图片社" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这部 12 集的剧集将讲述披头士乐队最著名的一些曲目</p><p>保罗<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/paul-mccartney-launches-a-life-in-lyrics-podcast-by-explaining-the-beatles-eleanor-rigby-3509327">·麦卡特尼 (Paul McCartney) 推出“A Life In Lyrics”播客，解释披头士乐队的“Eleanor Rigby”，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="音乐家保罗·麦卡特尼 (Paul McCartney) 于 2016 年 10 月 15 日在加利福尼亚州印第奥的帝国马球场进行沙漠之旅表演。图片来源：凯文·温特/盖蒂图片社" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-McCartney-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="/artists/paul-mccartney">保罗·麦卡特尼 (Paul McCartney)</a>今天（10 月 4 日）推出了他的“ <a href="https://www.iheart.com/podcast/1119-mccartney-a-life-in-lyric-119121943/">A Life In Lyrics</a> ”播客，第一集详细介绍了<a href="/artists/the-beatles">披头士乐队</a>“Eleanor Rigby”的创作过程。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-beatles-every-song-ranked-3121214">披头士乐队：每首歌按伟大程度排列</a></strong></li></ul><p>这个由 12 部分组成的系列节目改编自畅销书，由诗人 Paul Muldoon 主持，他为<em>《歌词：1956 年至今》撰写了前言，</em>将为听众提供无与伦比的机会来聆听麦卡特尼和马尔登。</p><p>在第一集中，Macca 分解了披头士乐队的曲目“Eleanor Rigby”。他解释了这首歌的标题的来源，并表示这首歌的名字来自他和已故乐队成员约翰·列侬看到的一座坟墓。</p><p> “约翰和我在一座坟墓周围闲逛，无休止地谈论我们的未来，”他在播客中回忆道。 “那里有一个坟墓（名字是埃莉诺·里格比）。我不记得曾经见过那个墓碑，但有人向我暗示，从心理上来说我会看到它” </p><p><iframe title="Spotify 嵌入：埃莉诺·里格比" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="152" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/2zKXwNasALPXEhMgoa9VIy?utm_source=oembed"></iframe></p><p>他还分享了著名歌词<em>“Wearing a Face That She Keeps in a Jar by the Door”</em>的出处，将这句话归功于他的母亲以及她对妮维雅冷霜的喜爱和使用。</p><p> “我妈妈最喜欢的是妮维雅，直到今天我仍然喜欢它。女人用了这么多冷霜，这让我有点害怕，当我长大并结婚时，我担心我会嫁给一个会[涂很多冷霜]并放了其中一种的人戴上大浴帽、卷发器，还有很多东西……所以这在我脑海中萦绕不去，所以她脸上的脸是放在门边的一个罐子里的，”他说。</p><p>马卡透露，他将这首歌曲设想为一部叙事电影，并表示：“我所看到的就像一部电影，只是在我的想象中。我有两个孤独的主角，她和他。你并不为他感到难过，但他很孤独。所以“现在所有孤独的人”变成了副歌……她死了，他埋葬了她，他从坟墓里走出来时擦着双手，“没有人得救”，这就是故事的结局”</p><p> Elsewhere in the episode, the legendary musician gave some insight on his love for songwriting “Oh my God, I wanted to become a person who wrote songs,” he said, “And I wanted to be someone whose life was in music.” </p><figure id="attachment_3509368" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3509368" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3509368" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/the-Beatles-posing.jpg" alt="The Beatles celebrate the completion of their new album, 'Sgt Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band', at a press conference held at the west London home of their manager Brian Epstein. The LP is released on June 1st. (Photo by John Pratt/Keystone/Getty Images)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/the-Beatles-posing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/the-Beatles-posing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/the-Beatles-posing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/the-Beatles-posing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/the-Beatles-posing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/the-Beatles-posing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3509368" class="wp-caption-text"> The Beatles celebrate the completion of their new album, &#39;Sgt Pepper&#39;s Lonely Hearts Club Band&#39;, at a press conference held at the west London home of their manager Brian Epstein. The LP is released on June 1st. (Photo by John Pratt/Keystone/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p> He also discussed his aversion to classical music training, explaining how the marjoity of musicians from his generation can&#39;t read music. He went on to say that when he is teaching a kid how to play piano, he usually shows them a few chords to get started. “You get C, D Minor, E Minor, F, G, A Minor, right there, that&#39;s like most of the Beatles songs. That&#39;s more than you need to know,” he said.</p><p> &#39;McCartney: A Life In Lyrics&#39; was co-produced by Pushkin Industries and iHeartPodcasts. Superfans can binge all of the first season immediately with a <a href="https://apple.co/pushkin" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://apple.co/pushkin&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1689781065014000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2DnsgGnaHsMUZ00XxCGW0b">Pushkin+ subscription</a> . A new episode will come out every week.</p><p> Season one will feature 12 episodes and Season 2 will follow with an additional 12 episodes set for release in February of 2024.</p><p> In other Beatles news, Ringo Starr has recently said that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ringo-starr-says-final-beatles-track-assisted-by-ai-should-have-been-out-already-3508409">the “final” Beatles song – which has been made with help from AI – “should have been out already”</a> .</p><p> Speaking as part of a new interview with <a href="https://apnews.com/article/beatles-ringo-starr-interview-rewind-forward-6fc5236cb2a316775fe0723712fc3e41" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>AP News</em></a> , Starr has shed light on the supposed release date for the long-awaited track – explaining that it was supposed to have been already released by now.</p><p> “The rumours were that we just made it up. Like we would do that anyway… This is the last track, ever, that you&#39;ll get the four Beatles on the track. John, Paul, George, and Ringo.”</p><p> When asked about when fans can expect to hear the track or find out the title, he responded: “It should&#39;ve been out already.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/paul-mccartney-launches-a-life-in-lyrics-podcast-by-explaining-the-beatles-eleanor-rigby-3509327">Paul McCartney launches &#39;A Life In Lyrics&#39; podcast by explaining The Beatles&#39; &#39;Eleanor Rigby&#39;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
